 .SH DESCRIPTION
 \fBAnalog\fP is a program for analyzing log files, and is designed to be fast 
 and to produce attractive statistics.
 
+The normal invocation is just:
+
+.RS
+.B analog\fP [\fB-G\fP] [\fB+g\fP\fIfilename\fP]
+.RE
+
+Most of the switch options in the synopsis above have two forms; the one shown
+is with with "-" for turning off a feature, and another with "+" for
+turning the feature on.  Both versions are described in the OPTIONS
+section a bit further on.
+
 The usual (and easier) way of configuring \fBanalog\fP is through a
 configuration file, not command line options.
